headline: Flight Attendants Union Sees Opening at Delta: Labor Fight’s Next Phase
summary: Delta's non-unionized flight attendants could make another push to organize "in a few months," said Sara Nelson, head of a 55,000-member union. Nelson cited broader public support for labor as one driver of change.
